NAN G. DARSEY v. J. P. DARSEY 26 So. (2nd) 505

June Term, 1946

June 11, 1946 Spceial Division A Rehearing denied July 8, 1946 Cordon R. Broome and C. W. Peters, for appellant. Frank Clark, Jr., for appellee. PER CURIAM:

The question involved in this case is whether a common law marriage existed. The master, as well as the chancellor, found there was none. We find no error in the decree and the same is affirmed, without prejudice to any action which may be brought by either party on accounts existing between them.

*524CHAPMAN, C. J., TERRELL, THOMAS and ADAMS, JJ., concur.
